BifrÃ¶st: an imperative language -> hardware compiler.

Named after the bridge connecting Midgard and Asgard. You are free to  decide
which end is which in the context of HFL and the language created here...

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
QUICK EXAMPLE
$ make
$ ./bifrost examples/fib/*.prog
$ fl -f examples/fib/simulate.fl
$ make distclean
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Dependencies:
- Haskell platform
- bnfc ("The BNF Converter", on Ubuntu: apt install bnfc)

Build:
$ make

Usage:
$ ./bifrost [FILE...]

Examples:
See the "examples" directory.

Clean up everything for git:
$ make distclean

Troubleshooting:
- An apparent bug in BNFC causes a crash (e.g. "compile: Lang/LexLang.x:(81,13)-(87,20): Non-exhaustive patterns in case") if one feeds it certain sequences of symbols involving "$". One such sequence is the mistyped scissors "--$<--" (should be "--%<--"), so please don't run with scissors.